    "body": "### Problem\n\n\n\nNotes:\n* Sorry if duplicate or already closed, I tried to find dups but there was too many issues when searching.\n* I can't confirm that the problem is reproducible on [master](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/releases/nightly) or [latest stable](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/releases/stable) release, since I didn't build one of them\n\n**As a user, neovim panics when overwriting the global variable `vim`.**\n\n#### Output:\n\n```\nError executing vim.schedule lua callback: vim/_editor.lua:0: attempt to index global 'vim' (a nil value)                                                       \nstack traceback:                                                                                                                                                \n        vim/_editor.lua: in function <vim/_editor.lua:0>\n```\n\nThen neovim panics and shows this message before quitting with exit code `1`:\n\n```\nPANIC: unprotected error in call to Lua API (attempt to index a nil value)\n```\n\nAfter the error message there is no carriage return, so the user comes back to the shell with unaligned prompt.\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim -u NONE\n:lua vim=nil\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nEither:\n* A friendly nvim error message \"Not possible to set global `vim` variable\" (but I guess it's not so simple);\n* A better handled panic, at least with a carriage return, maybe with an explanation message\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.4 Build type: RelWithDebInfo LuaJIT 2.1.1753364724\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nIt works a bit better (vim version = 9.1.1975); The editor continues to work, but when running `lua print(vim)` it crashes with message  \"Vim: Caught deadly signal ABRT\". I didn't test it further.\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nManjaro Linux 25.0.10\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.42.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nscreen-256color\n\n### Installation\n\npacman -S neovim",
