            "body": "> A friendly nvim error message \"Not possible to set global vim variable\" (but I guess it's not so simple);\n\n~~Actually it is possible, Nvim just need to override `__newindex` metamethod of `_G` table~~\n\nEdit: `__newindex` doesn't work for existing key. But global `vim` can still be protected (so `:lua vim = nil` is no-op, and doesn't yield any errors)\n\n```lua\nlocal builtin_vim = vim\n\nsetmetatable(_G, {\n  __index = function(t, k)\n        if k == \"vim\" then\n\t\t\treturn builtin_vim\n        else\n\t\t\treturn rawget(t, k)\n        end\n  end\n})\n```\nNote that this still doesn't prevent users from setting any fields of the `vim` table, e.g `vim.api = 1`",
